HEADWORD: blended
<hw>blended</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>combined or mixed
together so that the constituent parts are indistinguishable. Antonym of
<ant>unblended</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>alloyed</stype>;
<stype>emulsified</stype>; <stype>homogenized</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mingled, commingled.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

